{"word":"στερέω","slug":"στερέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στερέω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to deprive, bereave, rob of</i> anything, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be deprived, bereaved</i> or <i>robbed of</i> anything, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to take away</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to have taken from one</i>, <el>βίον στερείς</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b> <p/></div>"}]}